    "body": "I think we need to preserve the invariant that `hash_tree_root(signed_shard_block.message) == hash_tree_root(shard_block_header)`.\r\n\r\nCan we do this by having a special SSZ list type that doesn't use mix-in?\r\n\r\nOr maybe we should use a `Vector` here inside the consensus object but send a network version of the block that is type `list` (for bandwidth savings in the event that blocks aren't full) <-- or just rely on decent compression from snappy\r\n\r\ncc: @protolambda ",
